'''Peter Beardsley's International Football''' is a [[association football|football]] [[video game]] developed in 1988 by [[Grandslam Entertainment|Grandslam]] and endorsed by [[Peter Beardsley]].<ref>[https://www.lemon64.com/games/details.php?ID=1914 Game entry] at lemon64</ref>

== Gameplay ==
Players select an international team to play as, and can choose to play against the computer in a one player league format, or two players in a two player league format. They can then select the other teams in each group. <ref>[http://www.zzap64.co.uk/cgi-bin/displaypage.pl?issue=044&page=028&thumbstart=0&magazine=zzap Page 28 Issue 44 Review] by [[Zzap!64]]</ref>

== Reception ==

The [[Commodore 64]] version was reviewed poorly by ''[[Zzap!64]]'', which gave it a score of 23%, stating that it is "one of the worst football games around at the moment".<ref>[http://www.zzap64.co.uk/cgi-bin/displaypage.pl?issue=044&page=029&magazine=zzap Page 29 Issue 44 Review] by [[Zzap!64]]</ref>

